OL,3,CEsther Rantzen would choose to die in
OL,4,CJersey if law changes
OL,6,F"What always tips the balance for me
OL,7,Fis the personal stories from loving
OL,8,Ffamilies who've had to watch people
OL,9,Fthey deeply care about wrestling with
OL,10,Fterrible pain and suffering rather
OL,11,Fthan the quick and peaceful death that
OL,12,Fthey're begging for because nobody can
OL,13,Flegally assist them."
OL,15,FDame Esther lives in the UK but says
OL,16,Fshe would travel to Jersey to end her
OL,17,Flife if it became possible.
