OL,3,CEsther Rantzen would choose to die in
OL,4,CJersey if law changes
OL,6,FShe explains: "If that was an option,
OL,7,Fyes of course I would because my ideal
OL,8,Fdeath is to be somewhere with a
OL,9,Fbeautiful view, hopefully listening to
OL,10,Fmy favourite piece of music with my
OL,11,Floving family around me to say
OL,12,Fgoodbye. I can't think of a better
OL,13,Fdeath but only if Jersey want me.
OL,15,F"Jersey's always been very welcoming
OL,16,Fand hospitable and I'd be very
OL,17,Fsurprised if they turned me away."
