OL,3,CEsther Rantzen would choose to die in
OL,4,CJersey if law changes
OL,6,FDame Esther's late husband Desmond
OL,7,FWilcox campaigned for a change in the
OL,8,Flaw in the UK and she will be thinking
OL,9,Fof him as politicians start debating
OL,10,Fon Tuesday 21 May which was his
OL,11,Fbirthday.
OL,13,FShe adds: "He was an ardent campaigner
OL,14,Ffor an assisted death and of course
OL,15,Fwas not allowed one because he died in
OL,16,F2000 in London very suddenly. Although
OL,17,Fhis suffering wasn't prolonged, it
OL,18,Fwasn't the way he would have wanted it
OL,19,Fso in his memory, I will be praying
OL,20,Fthat Jersey comes to the right
OL,21,Fdecision.
