OL,3,CEsther Rantzen would choose to die in
OL,4,CJersey if law changes
OL,6,F"The right decision for Jersey, I
OL,7,Fwouldn't want to impose my choice on
OL,8,Fanybody else but I do hope people who
OL,9,Fagree with me get a guaranteed good
OL,10,Fdeath and can face the future with
OL,11,Fconfidence."
OL,13,FHowever, the issue of legalising
OL,14,Fassisted dying is deeply contested
OL,15,Fwith strongly held views on both sides.
OL,17,FThose against a change in the law
OL,18,Fargue vulnerable people would be put
OL,19,Fat risk and may feel pressured into an
OL,20,Fassisted death.
